  "prompt": "What are some signs that a woman is on her period?",
  "response": "Here are some common signs that a woman may be on her period:\n\n1. **Menstrual Bleeding**: The most obvious sign is vaginal bleeding, which can vary from light spotting to heavy flow.\n\n2. **Cramps**: Many women experience menstrual cramps, which can range from mild to severe abdominal pain.\n\n3. **Mood Swings**: Hormonal fluctuations can lead to mood swings, irritability, or feelings of sadness.\n\n4. **Bloating and Water Retention**: Some women experience bloating and water retention, which can make them feel uncomfortable.\n\n5. **Breast Tenderness**: Hormonal changes can cause breasts to become tender or swollen.\n\n6. **Fatigue**: Many women feel more tired than usual during their period.\n\n7. **Headaches**: Some women experience headaches or migraines as a result of hormonal changes.\n\n8. **Food Cravings**: Changes in hormone levels can lead to cravings for certain foods, particularly sweets or salty snacks.\n\n9. **Acne**: Hormonal fluctuations can cause breakouts or worsen existing acne.\n\n10. **Changes in Bowel Habits**: Some women experience constipation or diarrhea during their period.\n\nIt's important to note that not all women experience all of these symptoms, and the severity and combination of symptoms can vary greatly from one woman to another. If you or someone you know is experiencing severe symptoms, it's a good idea to consult a healthcare provider.",
